OBJECTIVE: The objective of this systematic review is to apply COnsensus-based 
standards for the selection of health Measurement INstruments (COSMIN) 
methodology to review psychometric properties of patient-reported outcome 
measures (PROMs) of HIV-related stigma and/or discrimination.
INTRODUCTION: Due to the development of antiretroviral therapy, the life 
expectancy of people living with HIV is similar to the life expectancy of the 
rest of the population. However, HIV-related stigma and discrimination are still 
major barriers to improving the quality of life of persons living with HIV. 
